One thing I read and heard often when I first started my online boutique (prior to designing my own clothes) was to shop for your ideal customer, not for yourself. Ultimately, that business failed (due to several factors), but I took a different approach with @dressedinjoy - now, I am my ideal customer. 

I design things I want to wear and  it’s made such a huge difference in my business! My favorite color is green 💚 so this set was exactly what *I* wanted! Turns out, it’s what so many of my customers want too! Almost 600 pieces later, this set is my best selling style ✨ I went with  my gut and it paid off.

Make sure you listen to yourself as much as you listen to experts in your field because a lot of times, you know what’s best for you & your customer. ✨

I was 👉🏾👈🏾 close to talking myself out of how big of a deal this was. Sure, everyone who speaks on a panel at #Samsung837 gets their headshot shown on a billboard in Times Square, but for me, it’s way more than that.

I started sharing my story on Instagram because I wanted my community to see themselves in me. I’m just a regular girl from the south side of Chicago who had a dream and pushed past the fear and self-doubt to make them come true. I believed in myself and want YOU to know that believing in yourself is half the battle.

So it wasn’t *just* my picture on a digital billboard in Times Square (which is pretty amazing, in and of itself). It was the dedication I’ve had to encouraging others that there is NO TIMELINE for achieving your dreams. It was my vision to host an event where women of all ages and stages could be inspired by hearing from other trailblazing 40+ women. It was my courage and audacity to put myself out there and propose such an event.

All of this PLUS the billboard makes it the best view of 2023 for me. ✨
